Earlier projects, e.g., Cyc [lenat1995cyc] and ConceptNet [liu2004conceptnet], construct commonsense knowledge graphs (CSKGs) based on large-scale human annotations.
Crowdsourcing CSKG construction has been revived in the ATOMIC project [atomic,comet-atomic-2020]. CSK extraction from texts has been researched in WebChild [webchild], TupleKB [tuplekb], Quasimodo [quasimodo], ASER [zhang2020aser,ZHANG2022103740], TransOMCS [transomcs], GenericsKB [bhakthavatsalam2020genericskb], and Ascent [ascent,ascentpp].